request.description:
### Get User Profile

This endpoint retrieves the profile of a user based on the provided user ID.

#### Request

- Method: GET

- Endpoint: {{host}}/v1/user/:id/profile


#### Response

The response for this request can be described using the following JSON schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "_id": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "email": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "username": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "createdAt": {
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "profile": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "_id": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "displayName": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "birthday": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "interests": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "updatedAt": {
          "type": "integer"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Update User Profile

This endpoint allows the client to update the profile of a user by providing the user ID and the updated profile information.

#### Request Body

- `displayName` (string, required): The updated display name of the user.

- `photoUrl` (string, required): The URL of the user's updated profile photo.

- `birthday` (string, required): The updated birthday of the user.

- `interests` (array of strings, required): An array of the user's updated interests.


#### Path Parameters

- `id` (string, required): The ID of the user whose profile is being updated.


#### HTTP Request

``` http
PUT /v1/user/:id/profile

 ```

#### Example

``` json
{
  "displayName": "Rob Stark",
  "photoUrl": "https://nestjs.com",
  "birthday": "2000-09-21",
  "interests": ["music"]
}

 ```

#### Response (JSON Schema)

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "_id": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "displayName": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "birthday": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "interests": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "createdAt": {
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "__v": {
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "updatedAt": {
          "type": "integer"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

This endpoint allows the user to send a private message to a specific recipient. The request should be sent as an HTTP POST to the specified URL with the recipient's ID and the message in the request body.

### Request Body

- recipientId (string, required): The user ID of the recipient.

- message (string, required): The message to be sent.


### Response

The response for this request is a JSON object with the following properties:

- success (boolean): Indicates whether the request was successful.

- statusCode (integer): The status code of the response.

- message (string): Any additional message related to the response.

- data (null): This property will be null as there is no specific data returned for this request.


### JSON Schema

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "statusCode": {
            "type": "integer"
        },
        "message": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "data": {
            "type": "null"
        }
    }
}

 ```
